l did everything l said l would.
Don't follow me, because l'm finished.

497
00:54:12,849 --> 00:54:16,376
Have a nice life, have a nice death,
goodbye.

498
00:54:19,422 --> 00:54:23,825
There's no one on earth who'd
want this to be true more than me.

499
00:54:23,994 --> 00:54:27,020
You've got to be rational about this.

500
00:54:27,197 --> 00:54:30,223
Sam is no more in this room than...

501
00:54:33,136 --> 00:54:37,596
l understand the need
to hang on to him, l really do.

502
00:54:37,774 --> 00:54:43,076
- But this is absurd!
- lt seems absurd, but it had to be real.

503
00:54:43,246 --> 00:54:47,182
How could you believe
a fortune-teller from Brooklyn?

504
00:54:47,350 --> 00:54:52,811
- l watched them have a conversation.
- l don't buy it, not for a minute.

505
00:54:52,989 --> 00:54:56,425
- What about the things she knew?
- What things?

506
00:54:56,593 --> 00:55:02,259
The photo Sam took of me
on our trip to Reno. We were alone.

507
00:55:02,432 --> 00:55:06,368
And the green underwear
that l wrote my name in.

508
00:55:09,272 --> 00:55:11,467
She said Sam knew who killed him.

509
00:55:13,310 --> 00:55:18,179
- That he was set up.
- This is getting deranged.

510
00:55:18,348 --> 00:55:20,748
- She had a name and an address.
- Good, Molly...

511
00:55:20,917 --> 00:55:24,944
Willie Lopez,
303 Prospect Place, apt. 4D.

512
00:55:26,222 --> 00:55:30,784
- This is sick.
- Oh, Carl!

513
00:55:34,164 --> 00:55:37,361
Molly, l don't understand
how you could...

514
00:55:39,436 --> 00:55:42,030
..swallow this crap.

515
00:55:42,205 --> 00:55:44,867
This guy may not even exist.

516
00:55:45,041 --> 00:55:49,410
Maybe she's using you
to set someone up.

517
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:54,107
You're right. You're absolutely right.

518
00:55:54,284 --> 00:55:58,721
- That's what l've got to find out.
- How are you going to do that?

519
00:55:58,888 --> 00:56:01,482
She said Sam wants me
to go to the police.

520
00:56:01,658 --> 00:56:06,425
Sam wants you to go to the police?
Jesus, Moll... !

521
00:56:06,596 --> 00:56:08,655
What are you going to tell them?

522
00:56:08,832 --> 00:56:13,565
That some storefront psychic lady
has been communing with the dead?

523
00:56:13,737 --> 00:56:18,401
Do you know how that sounds?
You're talking ghosts here!

524
00:56:20,076 --> 00:56:21,668
l'm sorry,

525
00:56:21,845 --> 00:56:24,780
this really gets to me.

526
00:56:24,948 --> 00:56:29,510
- lt's OK if you don't believe me.
- l'm trying to, Molly.

527
00:56:33,056 --> 00:56:34,956
Look...

528
00:56:36,526 --> 00:56:41,293
..if it'll make you feel any better,
l'll go check this out.

529
00:56:41,464 --> 00:56:44,456
l want you to try and get some sleep.

530
00:56:44,634 --> 00:56:46,431
OK?

531
00:56:48,838 --> 00:56:52,239
l'll call you in the morning.
Goodnight.

532
00:57:19,302 --> 00:57:21,270
Be careful!

533
00:57:34,751 --> 00:57:38,812
Carl! What the hell
are you doing here?

534
00:57:40,557 --> 00:57:44,584
- Who have you been talking to?
- What do you mean?

535
00:57:44,761 --> 00:57:49,289
Some woman knows all about you.
Where's she getting it from?

536
00:57:49,466 --> 00:57:53,664
- l haven't said a word to anybody.
- She knows your name and address.

537
00:57:53,837 --> 00:58:00,333
- How do women know where l live?
- She knows about the murder!

538
00:58:00,510 --> 00:58:03,911
Now, l want you to find this bitch,
whoever she is,

539
00:58:04,080 --> 00:58:06,105
and l want you to...

540
00:58:08,051 --> 00:58:10,212
Just get rid of her, OK?

541
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:16,323
l've got 4 million dollars stuffed in
a goddamn computer.

542
00:58:16,493 --> 00:58:21,328
lf l don't get those codes,
if that money is not transferred soon...

543
00:58:23,266 --> 00:58:27,066
..l'm... dead. We're both dead.

544
00:58:27,237 --> 00:58:30,604
Tell them you only launder money
on the first of the month.

545
00:58:30,773 --> 00:58:35,608
What the hell is wrong with you?
ls everything a joke?

546
00:58:35,778 --> 00:58:39,441
You killed a man.
You were supposed to steal his wallet.

547
00:58:39,616 --> 00:58:42,414
l did you a favour, man,
that was a freebie.

548
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:46,678
Look, these are drug dealers, OK?

549
00:58:48,124 --> 00:58:52,117
Just don't blow this for me, Willie.
l'd lose my job, go to jail.

550
00:58:53,029 --> 00:58:55,520
$80,000 of that money is mine.

551
00:58:58,735 --> 00:59:02,671
Let me have the keys
to Sam's apartment,

552
00:59:02,839 --> 00:59:05,706
l'll get the address book myself, OK?

553
00:59:31,568 --> 00:59:35,698
You goddamn bastard! Why?

554
00:59:35,872 --> 00:59:39,831
You were my friend!

555
00:59:40,009 --> 00:59:42,500
l had a life, goddamn you!

556
00:59:42,679 --> 00:59:44,772
l had a life!

557
00:59:53,022 --> 00:59:56,549
l don't even believe
in this stuff myself.

558
00:59:56,726 --> 00:59:59,251
But she was real.

559
00:59:59,429 --> 01:00:02,364
Do you think l'd come here
if it wasn't real?

560
01:00:04,300 --> 01:00:08,828
You told me if l had any new
information, that l should come.

561
01:00:09,005 --> 01:00:11,166
So, here l am.

562
01:00:14,911 --> 01:00:20,816
l know how this sounds. l hear myself
saying it, and l want to cringe.

563
01:00:20,984 --> 01:00:26,354
But she knew things she couldn't have
known. Things Sam only said to me.

564
01:00:26,522 --> 01:00:29,855
According to this psychic lady,

565
01:00:30,026 --> 01:00:34,019
there are ghosts and spirits
all over the place?

566
01:00:34,197 --> 01:00:36,859
Watching us all the time?

567
01:00:39,602 --> 01:00:42,298
l'm never going
to get undressed again.

568
01:00:43,306 --> 01:00:47,936
Excuse me.
l've got more important things to do.

569
01:00:57,954 --> 01:01:03,449
The guy's name is Willie Lopez.
All l'm asking is for you to check it out.

570
01:01:03,626 --> 01:01:08,290
OK. You wait here and let me see
if the guy's got a record.

571
01:01:09,465 --> 01:01:11,831
Right.

572
01:02:12,895 --> 01:02:18,128
- Where's the file on Willie Lopez?
- There's no file for Willie Lopez.

573
01:02:18,301 --> 01:02:22,635
He was probably some old boyfriend
she was trying to get even with.

574
01:02:22,805 --> 01:02:26,764
This psychic woman's
got a long record.

575
01:02:26,943 --> 01:02:29,878
1 967, Shreveport.

576
01:02:30,046 --> 01:02:33,709
Forgery, selling of false lD.

577
01:02:33,883 --> 01:02:36,443
Served one year in 1 971 .

578
01:02:36,619 --> 01:02:39,179
Arrested for fraud,

579
01:02:39,355 --> 01:02:43,223
numbers racketeering,
served ten months, 1 974.

580
01:02:43,392 --> 01:02:47,158
- Look, this is impossible!
- lt goes on and on.

581
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:51,733
She knew things - private things.
How could she have known all that?

582
01:02:51,901 --> 01:02:54,267
A lot of times they read the obits.

583
01:02:54,437 --> 01:02:57,668
All she had to do
was see the word ''banker.'' Boom.

584
01:02:57,840 --> 01:03:02,436
They even go through your garbage
to find things they can use.

585
01:03:02,612 --> 01:03:06,446
Letters, old papers.
lt doesn't take much.

586
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:08,208
No.

587
01:03:09,886 --> 01:03:12,446
lt was real.

588
01:03:14,056 --> 01:03:19,119
She knew about a sweater l knitted.

589
01:03:19,295 --> 01:03:21,991
And songs we sang.

590
01:03:26,235 --> 01:03:30,501
The trip to Montego Bay.

591
01:03:30,673 --> 01:03:34,541
l'm sorry. l know this is hard.

592
01:03:34,710 --> 01:03:36,200
People want so much to believe.

593
01:03:36,379 --> 01:03:42,579
They're grieving, they're vulnerable.
And they will give anything

594
01:03:42,752 --> 01:03:48,987
for one last moment. Believe me,
these people know what they're doing.

595
01:03:49,158 --> 01:03:54,323
l know how you must feel,
but you know you can press charges.

596
01:03:58,100 --> 01:04:00,068
No.

597
01:04:02,972 --> 01:04:04,837
Thank you.

598
01:04:18,888 --> 01:04:21,049
Oh, God, let this be it.

599
01:04:33,603 --> 01:04:35,468
Yes!

600
01:04:47,149 --> 01:04:50,141
- Hello.
- Eddie, it's Carl Bruner.

601
01:04:50,319 --> 01:04:55,757
Everything's fine. We're all set.
What do you want me to do?

602
01:04:55,925 --> 01:04:59,725
l want you to transfer the money
into a single account

603
01:04:59,896 --> 01:05:02,763
under the name ´´Rita Miller. ´´

604
01:05:02,932 --> 01:05:06,459
Tomorrow, at five minutes
before closing, 3.55 pm,

605
01:05:06,636 --> 01:05:10,333
transfer the full account to
the First lsland Bank ofNassau,

606
01:05:10,506 --> 01:05:14,237
registry number 486-9580.

607
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:18,847
- Call us when it´s done.
- OK, l've got it.

608
01:05:19,015 --> 01:05:22,644
Just tell Mr Balistrari that there
won't be any more problems, OK.

609
01:05:22,818 --> 01:05:25,810
Yeah, l´ll do that. Good work.

610
01:06:25,548 --> 01:06:29,314
Molly, why can't you hear me?
l need you.

611
01:06:42,131 --> 01:06:45,328
- Who is it?
- lt´s Carl, Molly.

612
01:06:45,501 --> 01:06:49,267
No, don't open the goddamn door!
He's a murderer.

613
01:06:49,438 --> 01:06:52,965
Listen, l know it's late.
l'm sorry to disturb you.

614
01:06:53,142 --> 01:06:56,270
l've been thinking about you all day.

615
01:06:56,445 --> 01:06:59,744
l feel really lousy about last night.

616
01:06:59,915 --> 01:07:04,045
- This supernatural thing...
- Don't worry about it, really. lt's OK.

617
01:07:04,220 --> 01:07:08,054
lt's not. You needed me
to hear you, and l didn't.

618
01:07:08,224 --> 01:07:12,786
l wasn't there for you,
and that was wrong.

619
01:07:12,962 --> 01:07:16,420
lt's just... l just...

620
01:07:16,599 --> 01:07:19,966
l want you to know
that l'm your friend.

621
01:07:21,203 --> 01:07:23,433
- Thanks, Carl.
- You were never her friend.

622
01:07:23,606 --> 01:07:26,666
- That means a lot to me.
- Me, too.

623
01:07:26,842 --> 01:07:30,209
l've brought you some
Japanese apple pears.

624
01:07:32,448 --> 01:07:37,385
- Thanks, that's very sweet.
- Could l come in for a second?

625
01:07:37,553 --> 01:07:40,613
l won't stay long,
it's just been one of those days.

626
01:07:40,790 --> 01:07:43,657
- Yeah, come on in.
- No, Molly.

627
01:07:44,326 --> 01:07:47,193
You seem a little tense. Are you OK?

628
01:07:47,363 --> 01:07:53,632
No, l'm fine. lt's just...
What can l tell you? lt's been tough.

629
01:07:53,803 --> 01:07:55,566
lt still hurts so much.

630
01:07:55,738 --> 01:08:00,368
- You lying snake!
- On top of it, there's stuff at work.

631
01:08:00,543 --> 01:08:04,172
They've given me my own accounts,
which is good.

632
01:08:04,346 --> 01:08:06,906
But l just haven't really
had time to adjust,

633
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:10,348
to absorb everything.

634
01:08:13,556 --> 01:08:15,023
lt's no big deal.

635
01:08:27,136 --> 01:08:30,367
- Can l have a little more cream?
- Yeah.

636
01:08:31,740 --> 01:08:35,506
Oh, shit!
Jesus, l can't believe l did that.

637
01:08:35,678 --> 01:08:37,339
- Are you all right?
- l'm fine.

638
01:08:40,749 --> 01:08:45,015
- Let me throw that in the washer.
- Don't worry about it. lt's OK.

639
01:08:45,187 --> 01:08:49,123
- Can l get you another shirt?
- No, it'll dry in a minute.

640
01:08:54,897 --> 01:09:00,335
Where were you today? l thought
you were coming into the bank.

641
01:09:00,503 --> 01:09:05,941
l was supposed to, but l didn't
have time. l went to the police.

642
01:09:12,715 --> 01:09:16,947
You did? What did you tell them?
What did they say?

643
01:09:17,119 --> 01:09:19,610
lt was awful.

644
01:09:19,788 --> 01:09:23,246
l felt really stupid.

645
01:09:23,425 --> 01:09:28,260
They brought out a file on this woman
at least ten inches thick.

646
01:09:28,430 --> 01:09:30,955
- Rip-off artist, huh?
- No, Molly!

647
01:09:33,202 --> 01:09:38,162
You know, the sad thing
is that l believed her.

648
01:09:39,141 --> 01:09:41,109
Molly...

649
01:09:42,244 --> 01:09:45,543
..sometimes we need to believe.

650
01:09:45,714 --> 01:09:47,773
Why? What's the point?

651
01:09:47,950 --> 01:09:50,510
lt's not easy to face the realities of life.

652
01:09:50,686 --> 01:09:53,382
Sometimes you've
got to give yourself that.

653
01:09:53,556 --> 01:09:57,322
You've got to remember
the love you guys felt. That's real.

654
01:09:57,493 --> 01:10:00,724
Remember how good Sam was,
how much he loved you.

655
01:10:00,896 --> 01:10:05,162
You were everything to him, Molly.
You were his life.

656
01:10:18,914 --> 01:10:20,711
l feel so alone.

657
01:10:29,024 --> 01:10:32,221
You're not alone, OK.

658
01:10:32,394 --> 01:10:35,852
You've got your work - you're talented.
You're young.

659
01:10:36,665 --> 01:10:39,133
You're fantastically gorgeous.

660
01:10:40,669 --> 01:10:44,002
l don't know what's real anymore.

661
01:10:44,173 --> 01:10:46,403
l don't know what to think.

662
01:10:49,612 --> 01:10:52,103
Just think about Sam.

663
01:10:54,083 --> 01:10:59,419
Think about the time you two guys
had together. How wonderful that was.

664
01:11:03,225 --> 01:11:06,160
Let your feelings out, it's OK.

665
01:11:06,328 --> 01:11:09,320
Life turns on a dime.

666
01:11:10,499 --> 01:11:12,990
You know...?

667
01:11:15,304 --> 01:11:21,174
People think they're forever, that there
is always tomorrow. That's bullshit.

668
01:11:21,343 --> 01:11:24,870
Sam taught us that.

669
01:11:25,047 --> 01:11:27,072
We have to live for now.

670
01:11:29,985 --> 01:11:32,249
For today.

671
01:11:51,240 --> 01:11:53,708
- l can't. l'm sorry.
- lt's OK.

672
01:11:53,876 --> 01:11:57,403
- l can't, it's just too soon.
- lt's OK.

673
01:11:57,579 --> 01:12:00,309
You've been great, Carl.

674
01:12:02,785 --> 01:12:05,948
- But l need you to leave.
- lt's OK, l understand.

675
01:12:06,121 --> 01:12:08,112
Please...

676
01:12:13,796 --> 01:12:19,826
Could we just have dinner tomorrow?
Just talk.

677
01:12:20,002 --> 01:12:22,732
- Yeah, sure.
- Great.

678
01:13:31,840 --> 01:13:34,070
Hey!

679
01:13:36,845 --> 01:13:39,905
- Get off my train!
- No.

680
01:13:40,749 --> 01:13:42,307
Get off!

681
01:13:42,484 --> 01:13:45,214
Get off! Get off!

682
01:13:45,387 --> 01:13:47,855
Get off! Get out of here!

683
01:13:48,791 --> 01:13:50,452
- Get off!
- No.

684
01:13:50,626 --> 01:13:53,823
Show me how you do that.
l'm not leaving till you teach me.

685
01:13:53,996 --> 01:13:56,021
Get off!

686
01:13:56,198 --> 01:13:57,756
- No.
- Get off!

687
01:14:04,973 --> 01:14:08,067
You stubborn asshole!

688
01:14:10,546 --> 01:14:16,451
What the hell are you doing? You're
trying to move it with your fingers.

689
01:14:16,618 --> 01:14:18,848
You can't push it with your finger.
You're dead.

690
01:14:27,696 --> 01:14:33,100
lt's all in your mind. Your problem
is that you still think you're real.

691
01:14:33,268 --> 01:14:37,136
You think you're wearing those clothes?
That you're crouching there?

692
01:14:37,306 --> 01:14:42,300
Bullshit! You ain't got a body no more.
lt's all up here now.

693
01:14:42,478 --> 01:14:47,916
You want to move something, you've
got to move it with your mind. Focus!

694
01:14:48,083 --> 01:14:52,247
- How? How do you focus?
- l don't know how you focus.

695
01:14:52,421 --> 01:14:54,389
You just focus.

696
01:14:58,160 --> 01:14:59,559
How did you do that?

697
01:14:59,728 --> 01:15:03,459
You take all of your emotions,
all your anger, love, hate.

698
01:15:03,632 --> 01:15:06,999
Push it, down here
into the pit of your stomach,

699
01:15:07,169 --> 01:15:10,002
and then let it explode, like a reactor.

700
01:15:19,748 --> 01:15:21,545
Don't laugh!

701
01:15:45,841 --> 01:15:50,335
- Way to go, kid.
- l did it!

702
01:15:50,512 --> 01:15:51,672
l did it!

703
01:15:52,381 --> 01:15:54,849
Way to go.

704
01:16:00,756 --> 01:16:03,350
From your gut, like l told you.

705
01:16:06,128 --> 01:16:09,586
Give it time.
What else have you got?

706
01:16:17,539 --> 01:16:19,063
How long have you been here?

707
01:16:21,510 --> 01:16:23,478
Since they pushed me.

708
01:16:23,645 --> 01:16:26,341
- Someone pushed you?
- Yeah.

709
01:16:27,115 --> 01:16:29,583
- Who?
- You don't believe me?

710
01:16:29,751 --> 01:16:33,687
You think l fell? You think l jumped?
Well, fuck you!

711
01:16:33,855 --> 01:16:37,586
lt wasn't my time!
l wasn't supposed to go!

712
01:16:37,759 --> 01:16:40,057
l'm not supposed to be here.

713
01:16:49,705 --> 01:16:53,197
l'd give anything for a drag!

714
01:16:53,375 --> 01:16:57,505
- Just one drag.
- Are you all right?

715
01:16:57,679 --> 01:17:02,514
Who are you? Why are you
hounding me? Who sent you?

716
01:17:04,553 --> 01:17:07,021
Who sent you?

717
01:17:08,590 --> 01:17:14,153
Leave me alone!

718
01:18:13,855 --> 01:18:17,313
Concentrate, and you'll
probably rouse him.

719
01:18:17,492 --> 01:18:20,984
- What's his name again?
- Orlando.

720
01:18:21,163 --> 01:18:24,758
Orlando, Orlando.
ls there an Orlando here?

721
01:18:24,933 --> 01:18:27,128
- l'm here.
- He's here.

722
01:18:27,302 --> 01:18:31,500
- Sam!
- l'm Orlando. The line's over there.

723
01:18:31,673 --> 01:18:35,939
Where did these ghosts come from?
You can hear them, too?

724
01:18:36,111 --> 01:18:40,070
ln the morning and in the evening.
They come into the shower!

725
01:18:40,248 --> 01:18:43,706
Did you tell every spook in the world
about me?

726
01:18:43,885 --> 01:18:48,720
l got spooks from Jersey. There's stuff
going on you wouldn't believe.

727
01:18:48,890 --> 01:18:53,657
- lt's amazing. You're really doing it!
- Can you please hurry this up?

728
01:18:53,829 --> 01:18:55,854
Chill out!

729
01:18:56,031 --> 01:18:59,398
l need your help again.
There's something we need to do.

730
01:18:59,568 --> 01:19:01,934
l'm not doing anything else with you.

731
01:19:02,104 --> 01:19:07,804
You're holding on to a life that doesn't
want you anymore. Give up the ghost.

732
01:19:07,976 --> 01:19:13,004
- Are you speaking to me?
- Does it look like l'm speaking to you?

733
01:19:13,181 --> 01:19:17,914
You're supposed to be concentrating.
Are you going to try it?

734
01:19:18,086 --> 01:19:20,748
Are you going to get out?
l've got work to do.

735
01:19:20,922 --> 01:19:25,757
Fine, then stay there.
Excuse me, are you ready now?

736
01:19:26,628 --> 01:19:28,357
Let's do it.

737
01:19:28,530 --> 01:19:32,830
Listen, l've got to talk to you now.
l've got a plan.

738
01:19:35,737 --> 01:19:38,331
Oda Mae?

739
01:19:43,578 --> 01:19:45,773
Oda Mae?

740
01:19:47,115 --> 01:19:49,413
Ortisha.

741
01:19:50,218 --> 01:19:54,518
- Orlando! ls that you?
- Where are you at? l can hardly see.

742
01:19:54,689 --> 01:19:59,058
- She's here!
- ln front of you. l'm right here!

743
01:20:03,431 --> 01:20:05,922
Damn, baby, what did you do
to your hair?

744
01:20:08,003 --> 01:20:12,133
Orlando, do you like it?
lt's autumn sunrise.

745
01:20:14,843 --> 01:20:18,074
Get out of me, you son of a bitch!

746
01:20:21,817 --> 01:20:25,082
- Don't ever do that to me again!
- Orlando...?

747
01:20:27,222 --> 01:20:29,122
l can barely move.

748
01:20:29,291 --> 01:20:33,227
You should know better.
Jumping into bodies wipes you out.

749
01:20:33,395 --> 01:20:38,264
- Everybody out!
- What happened to Orlando?

750
01:20:38,433 --> 01:20:42,130
Are you deaf? l said everybody out!

751
01:20:42,304 --> 01:20:47,241
Everybody out! Get out, get out!
Everybody get out!

752
01:20:58,887 --> 01:21:01,583
- Get out!
- Are you the fortune-teller?

753
01:21:01,756 --> 01:21:05,692
- Who are you?
- That's an interesting question.

754
01:21:06,294 --> 01:21:08,592
- Why don't you tell me?
- Willie.

755
01:21:08,763 --> 01:21:10,663
Willie?

756
01:21:10,832 --> 01:21:14,632
- Prospect Place Willie?
- Get out of here fast!

757
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:31,916
l'm all right.

758
01:21:34,155 --> 01:21:39,650
- We're in trouble. You have to help.
- Who's we? You're already dead.

759
01:21:39,828 --> 01:21:43,525
- They're trying to kill me!
- And they'll be back.

760
01:21:43,698 --> 01:21:47,156
Why don't you find a house to haunt?

761
01:21:47,335 --> 01:21:49,826
Get some chains and rattle them.

762
01:21:50,005 --> 01:21:53,236
l have a plan.
You've got to get some fake lDs.

763
01:21:53,408 --> 01:21:58,141
- Forget it.
- lf you do this, they'll leave you alone.

764
01:22:03,251 --> 01:22:04,878
Scout's honour.

765
01:22:06,154 --> 01:22:08,281
All right.

766
01:22:08,456 --> 01:22:11,084
What exactly do l have to do?

767
01:22:13,261 --> 01:22:14,853
Have you got a nice dress?

768
01:22:18,199 --> 01:22:23,136
- What's wrong with my clothes?
- l made a joke. l love your shoes.

769
01:22:23,305 --> 01:22:27,935
l'm going home. l don't know anything
about banking. l don't know if it'll work.

770
01:22:28,109 --> 01:22:30,737
- Just relax.
- l'm nervous.

771
01:22:30,912 --> 01:22:34,939
l know you're nervous,
but l'll get you through it.

772
01:22:35,116 --> 01:22:37,016
l don't think l should do this.

773
01:22:37,185 --> 01:22:42,248
- We're going to New Accounts.
- l'm giving them no money!

774
01:22:42,424 --> 01:22:45,120
Do what l say, and don't talk!

775
01:22:47,762 --> 01:22:50,162
You're here to fill out a signature card
for a new account.

776
01:22:50,332 --> 01:22:51,799
- Can l help you?
- Yes.

777
01:22:51,967 --> 01:22:55,494
l'm here to fill out
a card for a new account.

778
01:22:55,670 --> 01:22:59,731
- Do you know your account number?
- 926-31 043.

779
01:22:59,908 --> 01:23:03,571
926-31 043.

780
01:23:05,347 --> 01:23:07,178
- Rita Miller.
- What?

781
01:23:07,349 --> 01:23:08,907
Tell her Rita Miller.

782
01:23:09,084 --> 01:23:11,848
Didn't you sign when you
opened the account?

783
01:23:12,020 --> 01:23:14,648
Tell her Carl Bruner did it by phone.

784
01:23:14,823 --> 01:23:18,782
Carl Bruner opened that account
for me by phone,

785
01:23:18,960 --> 01:23:22,088
and he's asked me to come in today.

786
01:23:23,331 --> 01:23:25,765
- ls that right?
- Yeah.

787
01:23:27,769 --> 01:23:31,705
Just sign this card
on the bottom line, please.

788
01:23:31,873 --> 01:23:35,070
May l use your pen?

789
01:23:40,281 --> 01:23:42,977
No! Rita Miller!

790
01:23:43,151 --> 01:23:45,779
l'm so sorry.

791
01:23:45,954 --> 01:23:48,752
l need another one.
l signed the wrong name.

792
01:23:55,830 --> 01:23:59,561
Tell her to send it up to the third floor
file, you have a transaction to make.

793
01:23:59,734 --> 01:24:04,967
Make sure this goes to the third floor,
l have a transfusion to make.

794
01:24:05,807 --> 01:24:07,035
Let's go.

795
01:24:07,208 --> 01:24:09,938
You know what l mean... !
Can l keep this pen?

796
01:24:10,111 --> 01:24:14,912
- Yes, sure.
- Thank you so much.

797
01:24:16,084 --> 01:24:19,281
Bye-bye. l love these pens.

798
01:24:20,688 --> 01:24:22,417
What do you want to keep the pen for?

799
01:24:24,192 --> 01:24:27,787
Carl Bruner speaking. Mr Balistrari?

800
01:24:27,962 --> 01:24:30,362
Balistrari? lt´s me, John.

801
01:24:30,532 --> 01:24:32,864
John... Sorry!

802
01:24:33,034 --> 01:24:35,298
What's up?

803
01:24:35,470 --> 01:24:37,563
l´ve got the info
on the Bradley portfolio.

804
01:24:37,739 --> 01:24:43,041
- l'll pick it up later, all right?
- l´ll be here till six.

805
01:24:48,683 --> 01:24:51,777
l couldn't talk you into losing the hat?

806
01:24:51,953 --> 01:24:55,855
Keep messing with me,
you'll be here by yourself.

807
01:24:56,024 --> 01:25:01,052
You're here to see Lyle Ferguson.

808
01:25:01,229 --> 01:25:05,029
- l'm here to see Lyle Ferguson.
- Do you have an appointment?

809
01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:08,169
- No, l'm here for my health.
- Tell him Rita Miller's here!

810
01:25:08,336 --> 01:25:12,773
- Tell him Rita Miller's here.
- Just one moment, please.

811
01:25:12,941 --> 01:25:15,409
- Don't embellish.
- Jawohl!

812
01:25:15,577 --> 01:25:17,772
Excuse me?

813
01:25:20,215 --> 01:25:23,378
This guy Ferguson is a real jerk.

814
01:25:23,551 --> 01:25:26,486
l've known him five years.

815
01:25:26,654 --> 01:25:30,613
- Why are you whispering?
- Just listen!

816
01:25:30,792 --> 01:25:33,625
He's a social moron,
you've got nothing to worry about.

817
01:25:33,795 --> 01:25:41,031
Tell the guard Ferguson knows you,
from the Brewster's Christmas party.

818
01:25:41,202 --> 01:25:43,227
What is this in regards to?

819
01:25:43,404 --> 01:25:48,535
He doesn't remember me? We spent
time at the Brewster's, last Christmas.

820
01:25:48,710 --> 01:25:54,649
He and his lovely wife, Shirley. lt was
beautiful. A big old tree and presents...

821
01:25:58,086 --> 01:26:00,816
Gas!

822
01:26:00,989 --> 01:26:04,618
l get a little gas from time to time.

823
01:26:06,060 --> 01:26:10,190
- Quit poking me!
- Well, don't overdo it!

824
01:26:10,365 --> 01:26:16,270
Ferguson was so drunk, he could've
met Tina Turner and not remember.

825
01:26:22,744 --> 01:26:24,712
Here we go!

826
01:26:27,248 --> 01:26:29,910
Hello.

827
01:26:31,753 --> 01:26:35,211
Of course.
Well, it's been a long time.

828
01:26:35,390 --> 01:26:38,052
- Oh, a long time.
- Ask about Bobby and Snooky.

829
01:26:38,226 --> 01:26:42,754
- How are Bobby and Snooky?
- Fine... fine.

830
01:26:42,931 --> 01:26:45,729
Thank you for asking.

831
01:26:45,900 --> 01:26:49,131
And how is your...

832
01:26:49,304 --> 01:26:52,000
- ..family?
- Oh, couldn't be better.

833
01:26:52,173 --> 01:26:55,108
Well, wonderful.

834
01:26:55,276 --> 01:26:58,268
Ask how they did
on the Gibraltar Securities.

835
01:26:58,446 --> 01:27:02,542
l was wondering, how did you do
on the Gibraltar Securities?

836
01:27:02,717 --> 01:27:08,087
Gibraltar Securities? Well, it looks like
we topped out on that one.

837
01:27:08,256 --> 01:27:11,817
- We sure did.
- That was a very useful tip.

838
01:27:11,993 --> 01:27:14,484
Good old Randy.

839
01:27:14,662 --> 01:27:17,256
Got a good head
on his shoulders... her shoulders.

840
01:27:17,432 --> 01:27:19,992
- Her shoulders.
- Randy.

841
01:27:21,135 --> 01:27:25,629
So, what brings you here today?

842
01:27:25,807 --> 01:27:27,104
l'm closing an account.

843
01:27:27,275 --> 01:27:29,835
Do you have your account number?

844
01:27:30,011 --> 01:27:33,242
- Yes? Yes.
- 926-31 043.

845
01:27:33,414 --> 01:27:34,676
926...

846
01:27:34,849 --> 01:27:39,309
..31 043. ls that right?

847
01:27:47,662 --> 01:27:53,032
Well, Rita - it looks like you'll be
withdrawing four million dollars.

848
01:27:53,201 --> 01:27:56,364
- Four million dollars!
- Say yes.

849
01:27:56,537 --> 01:27:58,732
- ls that correct?
- Yes.

850
01:27:58,906 --> 01:28:04,469
Yes. That's correct.

851
01:28:07,849 --> 01:28:11,785
- How would you like that?
- Tens and twenties.

852
01:28:11,953 --> 01:28:14,114
- Pardon?
- Tell him a cashier's cheque.

853
01:28:14,289 --> 01:28:18,919
- A cashier's cheque.
- Cashier's cheque. Fine!

854
01:28:19,093 --> 01:28:23,223
Of course, you know
we require identification.

855
01:28:23,398 --> 01:28:27,732
lt's a procedural thing.

856
01:28:38,079 --> 01:28:41,742
Thank you. l'll be right back.

857
01:28:42,884 --> 01:28:45,250
Four million dollars!

858
01:28:51,359 --> 01:28:55,261
Get me the First lsland Bank
of Nassau. lt's on the Rolodex.

859
01:29:05,039 --> 01:29:08,497
Now, we have some things
for you to sign here.

860
01:29:08,676 --> 01:29:14,239
This officially closes the account.

861
01:29:14,415 --> 01:29:16,315
Sign ''Rita Miller.''

862
01:29:19,120 --> 01:29:21,179
Miller - that's my name.

863
01:29:21,356 --> 01:29:23,756
My name - Rita Miller.

864
01:29:23,925 --> 01:29:25,119
My name.

865
01:29:30,031 --> 01:29:33,125
l'll be right back.

866
01:29:33,301 --> 01:29:37,328
- Just anywhere?
- Right here.

867
01:29:41,709 --> 01:29:43,040
Fine.

868
01:29:43,211 --> 01:29:46,476
The cheque...

869
01:29:46,647 --> 01:29:49,912
..here you are.

870
01:29:58,893 --> 01:30:01,521
Mama took the money
from the oil wells,

871
01:30:01,696 --> 01:30:05,359
and she sunk it into gas pumps.

872
01:30:05,533 --> 01:30:09,367
And those gas stations have five
or six of those things, so it's lucrative.

873
01:30:09,537 --> 01:30:13,303
- Oda Mae, we've got to go.
- Got to go now.

874
01:30:13,474 --> 01:30:17,911
lt's been a pleasure doing business.
May l keep the pen?

875
01:30:18,846 --> 01:30:21,076
Say goodnight to Bobby
and Snooky for me.

876
01:30:21,249 --> 01:30:23,046
Bye-bye.

877
01:30:28,923 --> 01:30:30,914
What is wrong?

878
01:30:40,368 --> 01:30:43,166
Excuse me - Lyle?

879
01:30:43,337 --> 01:30:44,861
Molly Jensen.

880
01:30:45,039 --> 01:30:49,339
The woman you were doing business
with. What did she want?

881
01:30:49,510 --> 01:30:52,638
Did it have anything to do
with me or Sam?

882
01:30:52,814 --> 01:30:56,944
- Sam? No.
- That was Oda Mae Brown, right?

883
01:30:57,118 --> 01:31:01,384
Her name was Rita Miller.
She was closing an account.

884
01:31:01,556 --> 01:31:04,320
ls there a problem?

885
01:31:04,492 --> 01:31:07,120
No. l guess not.

886
01:31:37,458 --> 01:31:40,256
Carl? ls something wrong?

887
01:31:40,428 --> 01:31:43,591
Did somebody play
with the computers?

888
01:31:43,764 --> 01:31:47,165
- One of my accounts is closed.
- What's wrong?

889
01:31:47,335 --> 01:31:53,205
- Do you want me to call someone?
- lt's OK.

890
01:31:56,644 --> 01:32:00,239
Four million dollars! What am l
going to do with this money?

891
01:32:00,414 --> 01:32:03,315
l'm going to buy the building.
No, l'll buy the block.

892
01:32:03,484 --> 01:32:08,581
l'm going to make
my sister go to a fat farm.

893
01:32:08,756 --> 01:32:12,817
Wait, Oda Mae.
Take the cheque out of your purse.

894
01:32:12,994 --> 01:32:16,828
You're right, l'll put it
where nobody can get it.

895
01:32:16,998 --> 01:32:19,466
No. Endorse it.

896
01:32:20,401 --> 01:32:22,926
No, if l drop it,
then somebody will get it.

897
01:32:23,104 --> 01:32:27,040
lt's not yours.
l never said you would get the money.

898
01:32:27,975 --> 01:32:32,810
This is blood money. l was killed
for this money. Endorse the cheque.

899
01:32:32,980 --> 01:32:37,144
- What are you going to do with it?
- Look over there.

900
01:32:38,286 --> 01:32:39,810
To your left.

901
01:32:43,057 --> 01:32:47,323
You don't think l'm giving this
to a bunch of nuns?

902
01:32:47,495 --> 01:32:51,659
Otherwise they will track you down.
Your only protection is to get rid of it.

903
01:32:51,832 --> 01:32:54,426
You're kidding me!

904
01:32:54,602 --> 01:32:57,332
You'll go to heaven!

905
01:32:57,505 --> 01:33:00,838
l want to go to a bank
and cash this cheque.

906
01:33:04,612 --> 01:33:08,241
- Hello.
- You'll thank me later.

907
01:33:10,685 --> 01:33:13,620
- Endorse it ''Rita Miller.''
- l know!

908
01:33:13,788 --> 01:33:16,120
Make it out to St Joseph's Shelter.

909
01:33:16,290 --> 01:33:19,384
l don't believe
you're making me do this!

910
01:33:24,565 --> 01:33:27,932
- Give it to her.
- l just want to feel it in my fingers.

911
01:33:28,102 --> 01:33:31,469
- Just give her the cheque!
- l will!

912
01:33:38,613 --> 01:33:41,878
- Give her the cheque!
- l will!

913
01:33:44,552 --> 01:33:48,215
Bless you, child. Bless you.

914
01:33:53,561 --> 01:33:54,994
Give it to her.

915
01:33:55,696 --> 01:33:57,994
Let go. Let go!

916
01:34:05,306 --> 01:34:09,675
- l'm proud of you.
- l don't care. Stay away from me!

917
01:34:09,844 --> 01:34:13,143
What'll that nun do with it?
She can't go buy underwear!

918
01:34:13,314 --> 01:34:16,147
Leave me alone!
Never talk to me again.

919
01:34:16,317 --> 01:34:18,148
You're wonderful, Oda Mae!

920
01:34:54,288 --> 01:34:57,519
Go ahead, search! You'll never find it.

921
01:34:58,893 --> 01:35:04,695
They're going to kill you and Willie.
You're going to be fertiliser.

922
01:35:04,865 --> 01:35:08,096
They're going to bury you
next to Jimmy Hoffa.

923
01:35:51,879 --> 01:35:54,211
Who's doing that?

924
01:35:54,381 --> 01:35:57,009
Who's doing that?

925
01:36:12,032 --> 01:36:16,628
Hi. Where were you?
l thought we were having dinner.

926
01:36:16,804 --> 01:36:20,535
- Things got a little crazy, l forgot.
- A little trouble at the bank.

927
01:36:20,708 --> 01:36:25,975
l wish you'd have called.
l've been worried.

928
01:36:26,147 --> 01:36:30,743
- l've got to ask you about something.
- He needs to borrow $4,000,000.

929
01:36:30,918 --> 01:36:35,355
When you said you thought
Sam was talking to you,

930
01:36:35,523 --> 01:36:39,050
- what did he say to you?
- Why?

931
01:36:39,226 --> 01:36:44,323
Listen, l want to know exactly what
this psychic lady told you.

932
01:36:44,498 --> 01:36:46,989
Carl, let me go! Stop this!

933
01:36:49,804 --> 01:36:53,865
lt doesn't matter. lt wasn't real.

934
01:36:54,041 --> 01:36:56,635
What the hell's happened to you?

935
01:36:56,811 --> 01:37:00,303
Does this have anything to do
with her being at the bank today?

936
01:37:03,184 --> 01:37:05,345
At the bank?

937
01:37:05,519 --> 01:37:08,352
Ferguson said she closed an account.

938
01:37:08,856 --> 01:37:14,021
Her name isn't even Oda Mae Brown.
lt's Rita Miller.

939
01:37:17,131 --> 01:37:19,793
Carl. Are you all right?

940
01:37:21,702 --> 01:37:23,294
lt's just my stomach.

941
01:37:27,775 --> 01:37:30,869
Do you have some Pepto-Bismol?

942
01:37:31,045 --> 01:37:35,482
- Cyanide.
- lt's upstairs. Sit down, l'll get it.

943
01:37:41,755 --> 01:37:45,885
What's wrong?
Does little Carl have a tummy ache?

944
01:37:52,633 --> 01:37:55,033
Now do you believe in ghosts?

945
01:37:58,672 --> 01:38:00,867
l'll set the place on fire!

946
01:38:08,883 --> 01:38:11,215
- l'll cut her throat.
- Carl!

947
01:38:12,887 --> 01:38:17,654
l swear to God. l'll cut her throat.

948
01:38:19,226 --> 01:38:22,662
l need that money.
l want it tonight, at 1 1 o'clock.

949
01:38:22,830 --> 01:38:27,858
lf that psychic lady does not
bring it here, Molly is dead, OK?

950
01:38:28,769 --> 01:38:30,498
Carl, who are you talking to?

951
01:38:30,671 --> 01:38:33,936
Nothing. Molly, l have to go.

952
01:38:34,108 --> 01:38:37,305
l can't explain it now,
but there's a problem at the bank.

953
01:38:37,478 --> 01:38:41,380
- You're scaring me.
- l can't talk now, l'll be back.

954
01:38:41,548 --> 01:38:43,948
- Why not now?
- l can't talk now.

955
01:38:44,118 --> 01:38:50,318
l'll come back at 1 1 o'clock, OK?
l'm sorry, but it's really important.

956
01:38:50,491 --> 01:38:52,015
- Eleven!
- Oda Mae!

957
01:38:55,963 --> 01:39:01,128
l´m Arsenio Hall. Don´t try
to adjust your television. l´m black.

958
01:39:02,102 --> 01:39:06,038
- l want to watch ''Love Connection.''
- l love ''Love Connection.''

959
01:39:06,206 --> 01:39:08,868
Leave that! That's Arsenio.

960
01:39:09,043 --> 01:39:12,137
You love ''Love Connection,''
send your picture in.

961
01:39:12,313 --> 01:39:15,680
- She did!
- They just haven't answered yet.

962
01:39:15,849 --> 01:39:18,818
- Oda Mae!
- Sam?

963
01:39:18,986 --> 01:39:21,978
We're in trouble.
They want the cheque.

964
01:39:22,156 --> 01:39:26,490
The cheque you said
they would never know about?

965
01:39:26,660 --> 01:39:28,821
- What's happening?
- They're here!

966
01:39:28,996 --> 01:39:31,521
Get out of here, now! Go, go!

967
01:39:43,744 --> 01:39:45,974
